ZH: 我每天乘车上班。
EN: I take a bus to work every day.

ZH: 她坐火车乘车去北京。
EN: She takes a train to Beijing.

ZH: 昨天天气太热，乘车很难受。
EN: It was too hot yesterday, and it was uncomfortable to take a bus.

ZH: 我们可以乘车到达目的地。
EN: We can take a bus to reach our destination.

ZH: 在这个城市，乘车是最便捷的交通方式。
EN: Taking a bus is the most convenient way of transportation in this city.

ZH: 不要总是乘车，可以考虑骑自行车。
EN: Do not always take a bus, consider riding a bike.

ZH: 乘车时请系好安全带。
EN: Please fasten your seatbelt when taking a bus.

ZH: 我们乘车时聊着天。
EN: We chat while taking a bus.

ZH: 这次旅行我们打算乘车游览城市。
EN: We plan to take a bus to tour the city on this trip.

ZH: 他乘车途中睡着了。
EN: He fell asleep while taking a bus.

ZH: 乘车不但快捷还环保。
EN: Taking a bus is not only fast but also environmentally friendly.

ZH: 她从来不乘车，只喜欢骑自行车。
EN: She never takes a bus, she only likes to ride a bike.

ZH: 我们应该尽量乘车减少碳排放。
EN: We should try to take a bus to reduce carbon emissions.

ZH: 你乘车去机场要多久？
EN: How long does it take to take a bus to the airport?

ZH: 他因为坐迟了车而迟到了。
EN: He was late because he missed the bus.

ZH: 我们可以乘车到达这个景点。
EN: We can take a bus to reach this tourist attraction.

ZH: 乘车时间比较长，我们应该带些零食。
EN: The bus ride is quite long, we should bring some snacks.

ZH: 他宁愿乘车也不要打的。
EN: He would rather take a bus than take a taxi.

ZH: 她前往市中心需要乘车吗？
EN: Does she need to take a bus to go to the city center?

ZH: 我们要快点，不然就要错过乘车时间了。
EN: We need to hurry up, or we will miss the bus.
